1
00:00:47,590 --> 00:00:49,390
Are you really going to close the clinic like this?

2
00:00:50,090 --> 00:00:51,090
There is nothing I can do.

3
00:00:51,730 --> 00:00:53,559
The result of the disciplinary appeal...

4
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:55,300
won't be out for at least three months.

5
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,530
What will you do in the meantime?

6
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,270
Travelling? Studying?

7
00:01:01,740 --> 00:01:02,800
A side job.

8
00:01:03,610 --> 00:01:04,610
Excuse me?

9
00:01:05,710 --> 00:01:06,710
You know, right?

10
00:01:06,910 --> 00:01:08,310
Having multiple jobs is popular these days.

11
00:01:10,040 --> 00:01:11,410
What kind of side job will you do?

12
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:14,920
As a manager.

13
00:01:15,750 --> 00:01:16,750
What?

14
00:01:20,390 --> 00:01:22,520
This contract follows the standard manager contract.

15
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:25,190
Since it is a special situation, I added a few special clauses.

16
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:26,960
Please check them.

17
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:40,309
It's not the place which does cheating,

18
00:01:40,310 --> 00:01:41,940
so you don't need to feel distressed.

19
00:01:44,810 --> 00:01:45,880
Did you read my mind again?

20
00:01:57,990 --> 00:02:00,530
I clearly heard that the pay would be the best in the industry.

21
00:02:00,860 --> 00:02:03,100
I also clearly heard that you had enough money.

22
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:07,170
I clearly stated the premise that it would not be as much as yours.

23
00:02:07,570 --> 00:02:08,570
But unfortunately,

24
00:02:08,571 --> 00:02:09,870
you would know that it's currently under provisional attachment.

25
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:16,540
The contract period is exactly three months.

26
00:02:17,650 --> 00:02:18,879
Understood. By then,

27
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,179
I will have successfully returned,

28
00:02:20,180 --> 00:02:21,420
and I won't ask you to stay for me.

29
00:02:23,380 --> 00:02:25,520
Do you have anything else you want to add?

30
00:02:28,990 --> 00:02:30,330
Just one thing.

31
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:32,990
Please keep it a secret to my family.

32
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:36,260
Especially to my sister.

33
00:02:39,070 --> 00:02:40,999
That is not difficult,

34
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,940
but why are you so serious?

35
00:02:43,370 --> 00:02:45,110
You are scaring the person receiving the emotional transference.

36
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:48,040
Indeed.

37
00:02:54,080 --> 00:02:55,080
Here.

38
00:03:06,090 --> 00:03:07,100
What is this?

39
00:03:07,730 --> 00:03:08,860
Did you not read the special agreement?

40
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:11,729
It says that besides basic manager duties, you need...

41
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:14,440
to cover my acting skills through emotional transference.

42
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:16,799
I thought I just had to read the script and...

43
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,270
transfer my emotions to you. Did I understand wrongly?

44
00:03:19,270 --> 00:03:21,580
Does this person think acting only requires emotions?

45
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:24,780
Emotions, vocalization, physical expression.

46
00:03:26,550 --> 00:03:27,550
Sit here.

47
00:03:28,350 --> 00:03:29,350
Okay.

48
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:38,259
Even if I receive emotions,

49
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:40,399
it is important for us to work together...

50
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,530
to give them my best performance, right?

51
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:48,669
Yes. - If you make me...

52
00:03:48,670 --> 00:03:50,339
feel the emotions, I will try to match...

53
00:03:50,340 --> 00:03:52,270
the vocalization and physical expression.

54
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,280
Why do I have to do something like this?

55
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:00,310
Let's not think like that.

56
00:04:01,550 --> 00:04:02,750
It's petty.

57
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,650
Don't just carelessly leak my emotions.

58
00:04:07,390 --> 00:04:08,390
They're mine, after all.

59
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:10,790
The copyright of emotions belongs to me.

60
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:15,100
What can I do if I can't help hearing them?

61
00:04:18,730 --> 00:04:21,000
We're doing scene 19, which is in the dance studio.

62
00:04:21,269 --> 00:04:22,339
Hee Joo is packing her bag,

63
00:04:22,340 --> 00:04:24,609
and Yeon Ji is still holding out, not changing her clothes.

64
00:04:24,610 --> 00:04:26,440
If you smile to hide your emotions...

65
00:04:26,710 --> 00:04:27,940
Hee Joo must be packing her things.

66
00:04:28,410 --> 00:04:29,510
With a smile...

67
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:32,650
You should think if you're smiling because you're happy...

68
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:35,579
It says here, "with a smile."

69
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:36,580
Smiling because you're happy... - What?

70
00:04:38,890 --> 00:04:40,860
Me? Why?

71
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:42,860
I can't dance.

72
00:04:43,890 --> 00:04:44,930
Well...

73
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:49,229
So, the male lead's emotion here...

74
00:04:49,230 --> 00:04:50,930
is more like fear than hostility.

75
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,600
Do you understand?

76
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,269
Yes. - Okay.

77
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:56,240
Then you understood the male lead's character.

78
00:04:58,110 --> 00:04:59,310
By the way...

79
00:05:00,710 --> 00:05:02,540
What is the range of emotional transference?

80
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:07,349
I mean, if we are at opposite ends of the Earth,

81
00:05:07,350 --> 00:05:09,050
will emotional transference really work properly?

82
00:05:09,820 --> 00:05:12,449
We need to know the possible range so that even if something urgent...

83
00:05:12,450 --> 00:05:14,820
happens on set, we don't go beyond that distance.

84
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:24,400
Then let's test the range of emotional transference here.

85
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:28,070
Shall we start with 1 square, 10 meters?

86
00:05:28,340 --> 00:05:29,400
Yes.

87
00:05:36,580 --> 00:05:37,580
Two.

88
00:06:04,610 --> 00:06:05,910
Ten.

89
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:15,280
Here.

90
00:06:22,190 --> 00:06:23,590
I can't hear you.

91
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:40,680
That must be the limit.

92
00:06:41,010 --> 00:06:42,809
That is right. It is not possible up to 60 meters.

93
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:44,350
It seems to be possible exactly up to 50 meters.

94
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:46,449
So, even on set, I should not be...

95
00:06:46,450 --> 00:06:47,920
more than 50 meters away.

96
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:49,550
Then, you just should not be separated from me, Eun Hwan.

97
00:07:12,210 --> 00:07:14,580
Was my peace of mind...

98
00:07:15,910 --> 00:07:16,980
conveyed to you?

99
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:32,390
Come in.

100
00:07:32,990 --> 00:07:34,700
Ms. Yu Ji An. - Oh, yes.

101
00:07:43,340 --> 00:07:45,410
I am not really keen on it, but...

102
00:07:46,010 --> 00:07:47,539
our writer and director...

103
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:49,040
recommended you so much.

104
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:53,280
I said her acting is better than expected.

105
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:56,080
Just trust my judgment this one time. Okay?

106
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,889
I'll see if it is worth carrying...

107
00:07:58,890 --> 00:08:01,890
that controversy. Let's see her acting.

108
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,269
I passed the audition.

109
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:46,529
I said I passed it.

110
00:08:46,530 --> 00:08:47,599
Passed.

111
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,500
I got cast. - Passed?

112
00:08:50,810 --> 00:08:52,270
Did you pass the audition?

113
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:01,420
Gosh.

114
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:04,150
That's great. Congratulations.

115
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:05,450
Gosh.

116
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,859
To begin my work in earnest,

117
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:16,160
I guess I'll have to buy a van, right?

118
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:18,830
No. Should I hire a stylist first?

119
00:09:19,570 --> 00:09:20,740
Which shop should I go to?

120
00:09:21,170 --> 00:09:22,370
Why are you in such a hurry?

121
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,840
It's just one drama casting that's been confirmed.

122
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:27,210
Let's take it slow.

123
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,740
You don't know what you are talking about.

124
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,679
Soon, there will be magazine shoots, commercial deals,

125
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,710
and even drama appearance offers pouring in.

126
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:35,519
Excuse me?

127
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:38,120
How common is an entertainer with star power as hot as mine?

128
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:40,349
They might have hesitated...

129
00:09:40,350 --> 00:09:41,719
because they were mindful of the public,

130
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:44,260
but now that the comeback signal has opened up. Then...

131
00:09:49,660 --> 00:09:50,799
Hello, this is Cha Eun Hwan. - Are you the person...

132
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:51,800
in charge of Yu Ji An?

133
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,500
Gosh, yes.

134
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:55,740
I am Yu Ji An's manager.

135
00:09:56,300 --> 00:09:58,410
I'm calling you to offer a photoshoot.

136
00:09:58,510 --> 00:09:59,510
What?

137
00:10:00,780 --> 00:10:02,140
A photoshoot?

138
00:10:16,260 --> 00:10:17,790
Yes, good. The pose is good now.

139
00:10:18,230 --> 00:10:19,289
Okay, good.

140
00:10:19,290 --> 00:10:20,290
We will go with that.

141
00:10:20,730 --> 00:10:22,199
Oh, that's pretty. Good.

142
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,200
Stay like that.

143
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,370
Oh, nice.

144
00:10:24,670 --> 00:10:27,270
Now, look the other way.

145
00:10:34,610 --> 00:10:36,110
I am so dumbfounded.

146
00:10:36,410 --> 00:10:38,150
Do you think I am the same as before?

147
00:10:38,350 --> 00:10:39,750
You are mistaken.

148
00:10:40,310 --> 00:10:41,350
I am fine.

149
00:10:42,020 --> 00:10:43,420
It is stranger that you are doing this.

150
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:45,190
You hurt my pride.

151
00:10:46,290 --> 00:10:48,219
No, I'm saying this...

152
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:51,330
because I misunderstood your... - There is no need for that.

153
00:10:51,690 --> 00:10:53,429
Do I really have to come out in this freezing cold...

154
00:10:53,430 --> 00:10:55,130
just to tell you that?

155
00:11:08,210 --> 00:11:09,639
A character like Hee Joo,

156
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:11,979
who always considers others' feelings first,

157
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:13,950
would not readily get angry in this situation.

158
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:16,980
So, even in that situation, she would unknowingly...

159
00:11:17,890 --> 00:11:19,490
just let out an awkward laugh.

160
00:11:20,090 --> 00:11:21,090
I see.

161
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:23,490
Can you understand that?

162
00:11:23,590 --> 00:11:24,660
Yes.

163
00:11:26,090 --> 00:11:28,059
But how do you know...

164
00:11:28,060 --> 00:11:29,830
other people's emotions so well?

165
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:36,200
Because I am a psychological counsellor, after all?

166
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:40,040
Is that empathy innate?

167
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:41,980
Or is it something you can learn?

168
00:11:44,010 --> 00:11:46,580
It is both innate and learned.

169
00:11:51,590 --> 00:11:53,350
My father was...

170
00:11:53,850 --> 00:11:55,090
that kind of person.

171
00:11:57,790 --> 00:12:00,960
Always putting others before himself.

172
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,160
He passed away, right?

173
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:13,270
I can feel that you are sad.

174
00:12:15,580 --> 00:12:17,780
Oh, yes.

175
00:12:19,710 --> 00:12:21,820
It was an accident in elementary school.

176
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:24,850
That must have been hard.

177
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,120
I didn't even deserve it.

178
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,160
It was all because of me.

179
00:12:35,300 --> 00:12:36,700
It was just out of curiosity.

180
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,500
I played with it out of curiosity and forgot.

181
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:47,140
Don't cause trouble while Dad is working.

182
00:12:47,780 --> 00:12:49,040
Just give him the lottery ticket and leave.

183
00:12:49,380 --> 00:12:50,379
Understood?

184
00:12:50,380 --> 00:12:51,380
I said I got it.

185
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:54,650
I said there was no problem, so let's proceed.

186
00:12:55,250 --> 00:12:56,820
Well, I'm telling you it's dangerous.

187
00:12:57,420 --> 00:13:00,250
No, the space is already cramped, and there's no ventilation.

188
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,219
What if it rains later?

189
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:03,490
I know, I know.

190
00:13:03,690 --> 00:13:05,790
It's not easy to stop filming here either.

191
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:07,260
Director.

192
00:13:07,590 --> 00:13:08,600
Oh, well.

193
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:15,200
Eun Hwan and Song Hwan.

194
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:18,570
What are you doing here? - Dad.

195
00:13:18,670 --> 00:13:19,739
Yes.

196
00:13:19,740 --> 00:13:20,810
What about your art competition?

197
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:22,810
I couldn't go because of him.

198
00:13:24,810 --> 00:13:26,150
What are you doing there? Give it to him quickly.

199
00:13:28,220 --> 00:13:29,220
What is it?

200
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:32,590
Eun Hwan was looking for toys in your room.

201
00:13:34,020 --> 00:13:35,460
The director is looking for you.

202
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:36,790
Oh, really?

203
00:13:37,060 --> 00:13:38,090
Dad will be right back.

204
00:13:38,730 --> 00:13:39,730
Let's go.

205
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:47,369
Take care of Eun Hwan.

206
00:13:47,370 --> 00:13:48,440
Dad, Dad.

207
00:13:49,370 --> 00:13:50,400
Dad, take this.

208
00:13:51,010 --> 00:13:52,010
No, Eun Hwan.

209
00:13:53,570 --> 00:13:55,380
I went to give it to him.

210
00:13:55,980 --> 00:13:57,210
Then the accident happened.

211
00:13:58,780 --> 00:14:00,210
Since that day, I always thought.

212
00:14:01,950 --> 00:14:04,350
If only I had not touched my father's respirator...

213
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:08,219
No, if only I...

214
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:10,020
If I had gone to give it to him alone...

215
00:14:12,230 --> 00:14:13,460
If only I had not...

216
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:17,460
let go of my sister's hand at that moment,

217
00:14:21,170 --> 00:14:22,670
all this misfortune...

218
00:14:23,770 --> 00:14:25,340
would have avoided us.

219
00:14:28,310 --> 00:14:30,440
I am the one who made the biggest mistake.

220
00:14:31,410 --> 00:14:32,410
Why am I the only one...

221
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,020
who is fine?

222
00:14:42,690 --> 00:14:43,960
But what right do I have to be struggling?

223
00:14:45,860 --> 00:14:46,860
How dare I.

224
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:58,409
I am not that sad.

225
00:14:58,410 --> 00:14:59,770
Why are you crying so much?

226
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:02,380
That emotional transference is malfunctioning.

227
00:15:04,580 --> 00:15:05,609
Tomorrow is the first shoot,

228
00:15:05,610 --> 00:15:06,680
and your eyes will be swollen because of me.

229
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:50,920
Shall I tell you...

230
00:15:51,430 --> 00:15:52,860
a secret?

231
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:59,070
If you make eye contact with me like this,

232
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:03,640
the emotional transference stops.

233
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:17,250
It is mine.

234
00:17:03,430 --> 00:17:07,329
How embarrassing.

235
00:17:18,250 --> 00:17:20,380
A kiss? What did I do to him?

236
00:17:21,550 --> 00:17:23,079
Should I just say it was a drunken mistake?

237
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:25,990
Oh, I only drink sparkling water.

238
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,560
What should I do?

239
00:17:38,030 --> 00:17:39,030
Gosh, I don't care anymore.

240
00:17:39,770 --> 00:17:40,800
I will just ignore it.

241
00:17:46,510 --> 00:17:47,510
Good morning.

242
00:17:54,410 --> 00:17:55,420
What was that?

243
00:17:55,980 --> 00:17:57,080
That sound just now?

244
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:15,200
All right, we will get ready.

245
00:18:16,940 --> 00:18:17,940
All right.

246
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,240
Ready.

247
00:18:26,650 --> 00:18:27,650
Action.

248
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,760
What is wrong with her? - Did she forget her lines?

249
00:18:42,860 --> 00:18:43,860
Should we show her the script?

250
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:45,429
What is she doing?

251
00:18:45,430 --> 00:18:46,430
Is she sick?

252
00:18:49,340 --> 00:18:50,340
What's going on?

253
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:53,740
Nothing at all... No emotions are conveyed.

254
00:19:05,050 --> 00:19:06,350
Yes, I am all ready.

255
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:10,059
Don't rush at the kids too obviously.

256
00:19:10,060 --> 00:19:11,460
Give it some time.

257
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:14,730
Rich kids should do it sincerely, right?

258
00:19:16,430 --> 00:19:17,459
Yes.

259
00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:27,870
What do you mean? We are not supporting the bullying issue.

260
00:19:28,710 --> 00:19:31,410
Currently, the facts have not been confirmed.

261
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:36,320
Hey, call them over right now.

262
00:19:36,950 --> 00:19:37,950
They are filming right now.

263
00:19:38,150 --> 00:19:39,249
Is filming the problem?

264
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:40,650
The real problem is that it can't be aired.

265
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,990
Yes, I understand.

266
00:19:47,190 --> 00:19:48,430
I am fine.

267
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:51,259
I think...

268
00:19:51,260 --> 00:19:53,770
I think I endured this much well. - Cut.

269
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:59,010
No, I said that's not the emotion.

270
00:19:59,870 --> 00:20:01,380
Oh, come on. Seriously.

271
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:04,080
All right, again.

272
00:20:07,450 --> 00:20:09,580
Ready, action.

273
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:11,250
I am fine.

274
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:13,850
I think I endured this much well. - Cut.

275
00:20:15,090 --> 00:20:16,289
Cut, cut.

276
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:17,290
All right, again.

277
00:20:18,090 --> 00:20:19,090
You can do it.

278
00:20:19,690 --> 00:20:20,690
Come on.

279
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:23,330
Oh, how many times has it been?

280
00:20:24,230 --> 00:20:25,270
Is her condition not good?

281
00:20:25,570 --> 00:20:26,570
Gosh. Why is she like that today?

282
00:20:27,170 --> 00:20:28,370
Let me go home. - All right.

283
00:20:28,970 --> 00:20:30,100
