545
00:36:08,170 --> 00:36:09,580
See, she is a liar.

546
00:36:10,140 --> 00:36:11,140
She's an orphan.

547
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,050
I am not an orphan.

548
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:14,750
I am not a liar.

549
00:36:15,210 --> 00:36:16,220
Hey, did you...

550
00:36:16,780 --> 00:36:17,780
Hey.

551
00:36:20,390 --> 00:36:21,719
You can't fight...

552
00:36:21,720 --> 00:36:23,690
in this sacred playground, kids.

553
00:36:24,090 --> 00:36:25,090
Who are you, ma'am?

554
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:27,360
Ma'am again?

555
00:36:27,790 --> 00:36:30,430
– Hey, I am not a ma'am. – She is my mom.

556
00:36:33,200 --> 00:36:34,230
Me?

557
00:36:41,340 --> 00:36:42,910
Oh, right.

558
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:44,680
I am Ha Yul's mother.

559
00:36:45,810 --> 00:36:47,050
Who bothered Ha Yul?

560
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:49,150
Was it you?

561
00:36:49,580 --> 00:36:50,580
Was it you?

562
00:37:04,630 --> 00:37:06,970
Little one, aren't you going home?

563
00:37:09,940 --> 00:37:10,940
Hey, it's late.

564
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:13,539
If you don't go home again, your mother will worry herself...

565
00:37:13,540 --> 00:37:15,070
to death, thinking you might have been in an accident.

566
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:18,440
My mother does not worry about me.

567
00:37:20,980 --> 00:37:22,680
Because she does not love me.

568
00:37:25,790 --> 00:37:28,689
No, there is no mother in the world...

569
00:37:28,690 --> 00:37:31,560
who does not love her child.

570
00:37:32,090 --> 00:37:33,260
You are lying.

571
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:36,800
Yes, that's right.

572
00:37:38,700 --> 00:37:39,700
That's a lie.

573
00:37:43,300 --> 00:37:45,909
There are mothers who love...

574
00:37:45,910 --> 00:37:52,010
themselves more than their children.

575
00:37:53,780 --> 00:37:54,780
Like someone.

576
00:37:55,310 --> 00:37:56,320
Gosh.

577
00:37:56,750 --> 00:37:57,750
It's okay.

578
00:37:59,050 --> 00:38:00,950
I don't love my mom either.

579
00:38:01,990 --> 00:38:02,990
You are lying too.

580
00:38:04,890 --> 00:38:06,389
There are mothers in this world...

581
00:38:06,390 --> 00:38:08,890
who don't love their children,

582
00:38:09,130 --> 00:38:11,700
but there is no seven-year-old...

583
00:38:13,300 --> 00:38:14,300
who does not love their mother.

584
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:18,100
I'm well aware of it.

585
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:26,850
I am depressed and want to cook.

586
00:38:27,350 --> 00:38:28,610
Would you like to go to my place and eat tteokbokki?

587
00:38:30,250 --> 00:38:32,350
Are you happy? Let's go.

588
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:34,320
You are cold, aren't you?

589
00:38:34,450 --> 00:38:35,990
Come here. Let's go.

590
00:38:37,760 --> 00:38:39,230
It's freezing.

591
00:38:42,460 --> 00:38:43,460
Ha Yul.

592
00:38:43,730 --> 00:38:45,030
It is Dad.

593
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,830
Ha Yul, let's eat tteokbokki next time.

594
00:38:48,300 --> 00:38:50,940
Why? Can't we eat with Dad?

595
00:38:51,140 --> 00:38:53,309
No, we can't. See you next time then.

596
00:38:53,310 --> 00:38:54,310
Little kid next door.

597
00:39:02,620 --> 00:39:05,020
Ha Yul, where did you go with the aunt next door?

598
00:39:05,620 --> 00:39:06,990
We met at the playground.

599
00:39:07,850 --> 00:39:10,590
Dad, did you fight with her?

600
00:39:11,460 --> 00:39:12,460
No, why?

601
00:39:12,690 --> 00:39:14,390
She ran away when she saw you.

602
00:39:16,060 --> 00:39:17,060
Really?

603
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:20,629
Ha Yul, do you want to have dinner...

604
00:39:20,630 --> 00:39:22,740
with Mom and the auntie today?

605
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:24,300
What about Dad?

606
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:27,070
Dad will have to go make up with her, right?

607
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:31,010
Ji An, please open the door.

608
00:39:32,580 --> 00:39:35,580
Ji An. Ji An.

609
00:39:37,450 --> 00:39:38,449
Why? What?

610
00:39:38,450 --> 00:39:39,450
What?

611
00:39:39,650 --> 00:39:40,790
Why aren't you answering your phone?

612
00:39:40,890 --> 00:39:41,990
You made me worry.

613
00:39:42,990 --> 00:39:44,420
You were worried about me?

614
00:39:47,530 --> 00:39:50,259
If my celebrity is out of contact,

615
00:39:50,260 --> 00:39:51,760
wouldn't the manager worry?

616
00:39:52,230 --> 00:39:53,230
That's dereliction of duty.

617
00:39:54,930 --> 00:39:57,739
Now that you've confirmed the celebrity is alive,

618
00:39:57,740 --> 00:40:00,210
you can go, Manager Cha. - What?

619
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:04,040
Are you angry right now?

620
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:06,410
No, I'm not angry.

621
00:40:10,180 --> 00:40:12,250
I think you are. I can feel it.

622
00:40:12,690 --> 00:40:13,690
I said I'm not angry.

623
00:40:14,190 --> 00:40:15,449
Why have you been looking at me like that?

624
00:40:15,450 --> 00:40:16,560
You are scaring me.

625
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:19,860
Shall I tell you a secret?

626
00:40:20,730 --> 00:40:22,359
If you make eye contact with me like this,

627
00:40:22,360 --> 00:40:24,000
the emotional transference stops.

628
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:26,500
You mean because of that?

629
00:40:27,070 --> 00:40:28,170
To stop the emotional transference?

630
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:31,240
Gosh, that is really petty.

631
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:34,009
You just let my emotions transfer to you without permission,

632
00:40:34,010 --> 00:40:35,139
but you are doing this...

633
00:40:35,140 --> 00:40:36,240
because you are afraid your emotions will transfer?

634
00:40:37,340 --> 00:40:38,580
So that is why you avoided my calls.

635
00:40:39,680 --> 00:40:40,950
Since you realise it, will you please leave?

636
00:40:41,410 --> 00:40:42,980
No, I won't.

637
00:40:43,720 --> 00:40:44,720
Come on. Let me go in.

638
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:52,960
I knew this would happen.

639
00:40:53,060 --> 00:40:54,260
How much did you drink?

640
00:40:55,890 --> 00:40:56,900
Are you addicted to sparkling water?

641
00:40:58,360 --> 00:40:59,670
It is none of your business.

642
00:41:00,800 --> 00:41:02,640
I am not just anyone. I am your manager.

643
00:41:06,910 --> 00:41:07,910
Cook for me.

644
00:41:08,710 --> 00:41:10,680
Is this a restaurant? Why me?

645
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:12,279
You said you feel better...

646
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:13,550
when someone eats something delicious in front of you.

647
00:41:14,580 --> 00:41:16,350
So what?

648
00:41:17,150 --> 00:41:18,720
To make me feel better?

649
00:41:21,820 --> 00:41:22,890
What nonsense.

650
00:41:23,090 --> 00:41:24,090
Oh, hurry up.

651
00:41:42,980 --> 00:41:44,280
Will just one cup of tea be enough?

652
00:41:45,140 --> 00:41:48,449
I am used to it, so it is fine. In a disaster like this,

653
00:41:48,450 --> 00:41:50,220
I must maintain my beauty.

654
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:55,650
I think you would be pretty even when you gain weight.

655
00:42:04,100 --> 00:42:07,100
It is not a heart-fluttering moment, but a thud.

656
00:42:07,800 --> 00:42:10,099
How can someone with such poor aesthetic taste...

657
00:42:10,100 --> 00:42:12,100
be my manager? What should I do?

658
00:42:13,140 --> 00:42:14,140
This way.

659
00:42:18,110 --> 00:42:19,110
Let's say that's true.

660
00:42:22,050 --> 00:42:24,520
So this is what it feels like for someone else to know my feelings.

661
00:42:26,990 --> 00:42:28,589
So you know...

662
00:42:28,590 --> 00:42:30,790
how uncomfortable I've been, right?

663
00:42:32,090 --> 00:42:34,459
And you know what a great sacrifice it was for me...

664
00:42:34,460 --> 00:42:37,230
to step up and be your manager despite that uncomfortableness.

665
00:42:39,770 --> 00:42:41,030
You're making a big deal out of it.

666
00:42:43,800 --> 00:42:45,970
You know I can hear everything.

667
00:42:46,770 --> 00:42:48,570
And you must also know that...

668
00:42:48,870 --> 00:42:50,380
I feel sorry for you.

669
00:42:57,150 --> 00:42:58,880
Are you really going to...

670
00:42:59,280 --> 00:43:00,590
give up to come back?

671
00:43:02,720 --> 00:43:05,190
You chased me around, begging for help with your comeback.

672
00:43:06,930 --> 00:43:08,390
I never chased you.

673
00:43:09,830 --> 00:43:12,060
It was just an active proposal.

674
00:43:12,460 --> 00:43:13,530
What?

675
00:43:14,230 --> 00:43:15,630
They said they don't want me.

676
00:43:16,670 --> 00:43:18,270
It's not about my acting skills.

677
00:43:20,540 --> 00:43:22,570
They say they hate my very existence.

678
00:43:24,240 --> 00:43:25,440
How can I make a comeback under that kind of reputation?

679
00:43:27,680 --> 00:43:29,380
And I won't be able to make a comeback for a while.

680
00:43:31,350 --> 00:43:33,689
If you try once like this,

681
00:43:33,690 --> 00:43:36,020
and then get forced out by public opinion,

682
00:43:36,720 --> 00:43:38,360
everyone plays it safe.

683
00:43:41,660 --> 00:43:42,660
What if I help you make a comeback?

684
00:43:44,260 --> 00:43:46,599
Within the three months as Ji An's manager,

685
00:43:46,600 --> 00:43:48,670
I will do whatever it takes to help Ji An make a comeback.

686
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:49,940
And I will do that successfully.

687
00:43:52,100 --> 00:43:54,669
Just as I believe in myself this much,

688
00:43:54,670 --> 00:43:56,940
Ji An, you should also believe in yourself.

689
00:43:58,380 --> 00:44:01,180
Nothing has been revealed yet.

690
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:21,300
Right, there is only one reason we gather here.

691
00:44:21,800 --> 00:44:24,000
To help Ji An make a successful comeback.

692
00:44:25,200 --> 00:44:27,139
After strategising all night...

693
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,070
Excuse me. - Yes, please speak.

694
00:44:29,310 --> 00:44:31,910
But why do we have to help her?

695
00:44:32,510 --> 00:44:35,450
Even Ha Yul and I.

696
00:44:39,790 --> 00:44:42,350
Of course. Yes, we must help her.

697
00:44:42,790 --> 00:44:44,859
Yes, of course. - This will be fun.

698
00:44:44,860 --> 00:44:45,919
How exciting.

699
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:46,930
Nice.

700
00:44:47,160 --> 00:44:49,489
The first strategy...

701
00:44:49,490 --> 00:44:51,360
for her comeback is...

702
00:44:53,230 --> 00:44:54,230
Take one each.

703
00:44:54,870 --> 00:44:56,570
Here.

704
00:44:57,540 --> 00:44:58,540
Look.

705
00:45:04,710 --> 00:45:06,780
A donation to the paediatric cancer ward five years ago.

706
00:45:07,350 --> 00:45:08,350
How did you find this?

707
00:45:08,480 --> 00:45:09,480
It was anonymous.

708
00:45:09,680 --> 00:45:11,649
I looked through Ji An's old records and...

709
00:45:11,650 --> 00:45:13,650
even interviews of hospital staff.

710
00:45:13,990 --> 00:45:15,190
You have quite a few donation records.

711
00:45:15,790 --> 00:45:17,360
There are many things I don't even remember.

712
00:45:18,060 --> 00:45:19,589
From now on, our job is to bring the...

713
00:45:19,590 --> 00:45:22,130
buried truth to the surface.

714
00:45:22,960 --> 00:45:25,699
We need to make people remember Ji An's true self,

715
00:45:25,700 --> 00:45:28,430
which they had forgotten or didn't know well.

716
00:45:29,300 --> 00:45:31,070
Shall we begin?

717
00:45:33,210 --> 00:45:34,370
Through various social media,

718
00:45:34,870 --> 00:45:36,909
creating natural buzz about Ji An...

719
00:45:36,910 --> 00:45:38,939
and favourable public opinion is the first step...

720
00:45:38,940 --> 00:45:41,010
to a successful comeback.

721
00:45:41,880 --> 00:45:44,419
Ji An's good deeds should be naturally...

722
00:45:44,420 --> 00:45:45,550
spread on social media.

723
00:45:46,350 --> 00:45:49,320
Will public opinion really change?

724
00:45:53,230 --> 00:45:54,260
We will make it change gradually.

725
00:45:58,430 --> 00:46:00,270
What are all these problems after recruiting a wrong person?

726
00:46:00,930 --> 00:46:02,830
Are you saying this video might not be true?

727
00:46:04,200 --> 00:46:05,870
The video itself was not manipulated.

728
00:46:06,870 --> 00:46:08,539
However, I will prove...

729
00:46:08,540 --> 00:46:11,410
that the video does not show Yu Ji An's power abuse.

730
00:46:12,310 --> 00:46:14,780
It will take more time to prove that,

731
00:46:15,380 --> 00:46:16,950
but please trust me just this once.

732
00:46:17,980 --> 00:46:19,319
All right.

733
00:46:19,320 --> 00:46:21,190
If you are so confident,

734
00:46:21,690 --> 00:46:22,990
let's go with the sole suspicion.

735
00:46:25,060 --> 00:46:27,289
Honestly, if it hadn't been for you back then,

736
00:46:27,290 --> 00:46:29,530
I would not have been able to continue working as a reporter.

737
00:46:30,930 --> 00:46:32,830
It seems it is my turn to repay that debt.

738
00:46:35,270 --> 00:46:36,670
Thank you.

739
00:46:36,940 --> 00:46:39,670
I will make sure you never regret that choice.

740
00:46:40,740 --> 00:46:42,910
Let's see.

741
00:46:45,280 --> 00:46:46,450
That's right.

742
00:46:46,980 --> 00:46:47,980
That's right.

743
00:46:48,110 --> 00:46:51,050
Yes. Last time, almost all of them were insults,

744
00:46:52,050 --> 00:46:53,220
but now it's half and half.

745
00:46:54,020 --> 00:46:55,020
Look.

746
00:46:55,590 --> 00:46:58,590
There are not many posts speaking ill of her anymore.

747
00:46:58,690 --> 00:46:59,690
Right?

748
00:47:01,190 --> 00:47:02,360
Check this out.

749
00:47:28,450 --> 00:47:30,719
So, Mr. Cha is...

750
00:47:30,720 --> 00:47:32,360
Yu Ji An's new manager?

751
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:34,860
Yes, that is how it turned out.

752
00:47:36,360 --> 00:47:37,360
No, how did that happen?

753
00:47:37,660 --> 00:47:40,000
A counsellor and a manager don't seem related at all.

754
00:47:40,700 --> 00:47:43,439
Well, if I were to explain, it's a...

755
00:47:43,440 --> 00:47:46,370
bit of a long story.

756
00:47:57,080 --> 00:47:58,280
I think it will be difficult.

757
00:48:01,090 --> 00:48:03,659
Of course, I promised Mr. Cha,

758
00:48:03,660 --> 00:48:06,220
and I'm also ambitious about the actress Yu Ji An.

759
00:48:07,030 --> 00:48:09,589
But in this situation, even if I am the director,

760
00:48:09,590 --> 00:48:11,330
it's hard to push it unilaterally.

761
00:48:12,630 --> 00:48:16,469
You seem to have misunderstood something.

762
00:48:16,470 --> 00:48:17,999
I'm not asking you to cast Ji An unconditionally...

763
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:20,240
with your authority as director.

764
00:48:22,140 --> 00:48:23,540
Just give her one chance.

765
00:48:25,310 --> 00:48:27,380
Let her audition for a supporting role.

766
00:48:27,910 --> 00:48:28,949
An audition?

767
00:48:28,950 --> 00:48:31,779
If Ji An earns the role through her skills at the audition,

768
00:48:31,780 --> 00:48:33,349
please ensure she can film without being removed...

769
00:48:33,350 --> 00:48:35,550
from the production, no matter what.

770
00:48:37,460 --> 00:48:39,460
That is all I ask.

771
00:48:41,690 --> 00:48:44,200
You want me to protect Yu Ji An with my authority?

772
00:48:47,230 --> 00:48:49,369
If she passes with her skills,

773
00:48:49,370 --> 00:48:51,040
I can take responsibility as the director.

774
00:48:51,740 --> 00:48:53,039
Anyway, last time,

775
00:48:53,040 --> 00:48:54,769
I let go of her too easily.

776
00:48:54,770 --> 00:48:55,870
I also feel sorry for that.

777
00:48:56,840 --> 00:48:59,510
But will Ji An audition for it?

778
00:49:01,110 --> 00:49:04,279
She was the top star...

779
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:05,450
in Korea.

780
00:49:09,090 --> 00:49:11,589
Are you crazy? Even though I dropped out, I was...

781
00:49:11,590 --> 00:49:13,559
the original lead in that movie.

782
00:49:13,560 --> 00:49:15,229
But you want me to audition for a supporting role?

783
00:49:15,230 --> 00:49:16,760
No. I won't do it.

784
00:49:18,260 --> 00:49:20,530
The drama you filmed before was also a supporting role.

785
00:49:22,300 --> 00:49:23,300
That is true, but...

786
00:49:23,500 --> 00:49:27,169
Then why do you think it's so embarrassing...

787
00:49:27,170 --> 00:49:28,240
and hurt your pride about this?

788
00:49:28,640 --> 00:49:30,280
It is not that I am embarrassed or hurt my pride.

789
00:49:30,410 --> 00:49:31,580
It's that feeling. I can feel it.

790
00:49:34,450 --> 00:49:37,120
Because the female lead of the movie is Han Yi Jin?

791
00:49:38,123 --> 00:49:39,783
Is that so important?

792
00:49:41,350 --> 00:49:44,889
It is important. Since my debut, I have never...

793
00:49:44,890 --> 00:49:46,220
been pushed aside by her.

794
00:49:46,530 --> 00:49:48,690
Then, get pushed aside this time. - What?

795
00:49:49,330 --> 00:49:50,829
Just because you haven't been pushed aside until now...

796
00:49:50,830 --> 00:49:52,260
doesn't mean you never will be.

797
00:49:53,836 --> 00:49:55,134
Look, Cha Eun Hwan.

798
00:49:55,135 --> 00:49:57,533
You have to experience being pushed aside and rejected.

799
00:49:57,534 --> 00:49:59,104
It will enrich your emotions.

800
00:50:00,170 --> 00:50:01,570
You said you want to act well.

801
00:50:02,070 --> 00:50:03,609
But how can you act well...

802
00:50:03,610 --> 00:50:04,710
if you don't even know such emotions?

803
00:50:07,050 --> 00:50:08,450
The role is good.

804
00:50:09,250 --> 00:50:12,180
I may not know about movies, but I know emotions well.

805
00:50:13,320 --> 00:50:15,349
Although it is a supporting role, there are many emotions...

806
00:50:15,350 --> 00:50:18,159
that can be expressed. If I convey the emotions to you,

807
00:50:18,160 --> 00:50:20,259
and Ji An expresses them well,

808
00:50:20,260 --> 00:50:22,560
I think you can be recognised by the public for your acting skills.

809
00:50:23,960 --> 00:50:28,030
You wanted to be a talented actress.

810
00:50:36,270 --> 00:50:37,280
Okay.

811
00:50:38,010 --> 00:50:39,210
This is as far as persuasion goes.

812
00:50:39,740 --> 00:50:41,050
I won't force you.

813
00:50:43,550 --> 00:50:46,750
How can I pass the audition without your emotional transference?

814
00:50:47,250 --> 00:50:49,050
Did you forget? The reversal?

815
00:50:55,760 --> 00:50:57,829
There must be some kind of rule...

816
00:50:57,830 --> 00:50:59,500
or reason we don't know about.

817
00:51:01,230 --> 00:51:02,329
But there is nothing in common between the day...

818
00:51:02,330 --> 00:51:04,439
the first emotional transference happened...

819
00:51:04,440 --> 00:51:07,610
and the day the reversal happened.

820
00:51:08,540 --> 00:51:11,209
The date, weather, time,

821
00:51:11,210 --> 00:51:13,750
place, situation... Nothing is the same.

822
00:51:21,650 --> 00:51:23,760
Why? Is there anything you can think of?

823
00:51:26,790 --> 00:51:27,790
Oh, no.

824
00:51:29,090 --> 00:51:30,900
Your face says otherwise.

825
00:51:31,660 --> 00:51:32,800
What is it? Tell me.

826
00:51:37,270 --> 00:51:39,340
Then listen without misunderstanding.

827
00:51:41,770 --> 00:51:43,980
A kiss. - What?

828
00:51:44,710 --> 00:51:45,910
I said a kiss.

829
00:51:46,140 --> 00:51:47,779
The day the emotional transference began and...

830
00:51:47,780 --> 00:51:49,179
the day the reverse transference occurred,

831
00:51:49,180 --> 00:51:52,850
the only thing we had in common was a kiss.

832
00:51:56,620 --> 00:51:57,820
Gosh, that's not it.

833
00:51:58,490 --> 00:51:59,490
What did you hear?

834
00:52:02,430 --> 00:52:03,900
Where is this guy trying to pull a trick?

835
00:52:04,700 --> 00:52:06,559
No. - My choice of words...

836
00:52:06,560 --> 00:52:08,030
was not that vulgar.

837
00:52:08,870 --> 00:52:10,840
Then do I look like I would not think that?

838
00:52:11,270 --> 00:52:12,739
You are lying in this urgent situation...

839
00:52:12,740 --> 00:52:15,510
to kiss me once. - Lying?

840
00:52:16,170 --> 00:52:17,180
Do you think I am a fool?

841
00:52:19,140 --> 00:52:20,150
Well,

842
00:52:20,810 --> 00:52:22,449
I admit to the second one,

843
00:52:22,450 --> 00:52:24,050
but we didn't kiss the first one.

844
00:52:24,480 --> 00:52:26,420
I lost my mind for a moment, but did I lose my memory?

845
00:52:26,920 --> 00:52:27,920
To forget that kiss.

846
00:52:29,590 --> 00:52:30,890
We did. We kissed.

847
00:52:31,690 --> 00:52:32,759
What?

848
00:52:32,760 --> 00:52:33,760
When you collapsed.

849
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:38,600
I am sorry.

850
00:52:44,600 --> 00:52:45,900
We did.

851
00:52:46,200 --> 00:52:47,410
We kissed.

852
00:52:47,940 --> 00:52:50,910
Then why did you run away when I kissed you?

853
00:52:52,210 --> 00:52:55,050
No, I didn't do the first one on purpose.

854
00:52:55,480 --> 00:52:57,580
I was just catching someone who was falling.

855
00:53:02,020 --> 00:53:04,090
What should we do now?

856
00:53:06,020 --> 00:53:07,030
Let's do it again then.

857
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:11,000
Let's do it. The kiss.

858
00:53:11,660 --> 00:53:13,400
How can you suggest a kiss so easily?

859
00:53:14,670 --> 00:53:15,670
You don't know my profession?

860
00:53:15,830 --> 00:53:16,840
I am an actress.

861
00:53:17,070 --> 00:53:18,700
I am famous for filming kiss scenes well.

862
00:53:19,270 --> 00:53:20,439
All other male actors who filmed with me...

863
00:53:20,440 --> 00:53:22,670
are known as kiss masters in the algorithm.

864
00:53:23,980 --> 00:53:25,379
Yes, yes. You are so good at it.

865
00:53:25,380 --> 00:53:26,440
You are amazing.

866
00:53:27,110 --> 00:53:29,480
Of course. It means I am professional.

867
00:53:30,010 --> 00:53:32,020
How can you be good at kiss scenes but not other acting?

868
00:53:32,720 --> 00:53:35,220
So let's do it. The kiss. Like a business.

869
00:53:35,550 --> 00:53:37,419
Why me? I am not an actor.

870
00:53:37,420 --> 00:53:38,820
You are my manager.

871
00:53:40,490 --> 00:53:41,989
For my acting career,

872
00:53:41,990 --> 00:53:44,130
you will actively cooperate. Did you forget?

873
00:53:48,070 --> 00:53:49,529
If you feel it is unfair, then you can...

874
00:53:49,530 --> 00:53:51,370
think of it as practising acting together.

875
00:53:55,740 --> 00:53:56,980
If you run away this time, you are dead.

876
00:53:58,810 --> 00:53:59,810
It is work, just work.
